From ad004e843c0488903f46ef47b9f94e466ea48714 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 15:44:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:hostapd: ucode: fix 320MHz channel switch
 disconnection

Due to wrong bandwidth passed from repeater STA CSA params to hostapd,
repeater AP channel switch fails and causes repeater STA to disconnect
when trying to set new CSA channel from root AP.

With proper bandwidth update for 320MHz, there is seamless CSA in the
repeater STA without disconnetion and same CSA done on repeater AP.

Signed-off-by: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ucode.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/ucode.c b/src/ap/ucode.c
index b911b9688a4e..88489d8bf1d9 100644
--- a/src/ap/ucode.c
+++ b/src/ap/ucode.c
@@ -746,7 +746,9 @@ uc_hostapd_iface_switch_channel(uc_vm_t *vm, size_t nargs)
 	intval = ucv_int64_get(ucv_object_get(info, "oper_chwidth", NULL));
 	if (errno)
 		intval = hostapd_get_oper_chwidth(conf);
-	if (intval)
+	if (intval == CONF_OPER_CHWIDTH_320MHZ)
+		csa.freq_params.bandwidth = 320;
+	else if (intval)
 		csa.freq_params.bandwidth = 40 << intval;
 	else
 		csa.freq_params.bandwidth = csa.freq_params.sec_channel_offset ? 40 : 20;
-- 
2.25.1

